Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.55,0:00:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rhythm of the wind clarifies all reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.18,0:00:07.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and causes alibi tricks to fall apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.81,0:00:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fortune-telling, an affair, and Three Kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.31,0:00:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All these things are connected to the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.14,0:00:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.02,0:00:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.98,0:00:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.53,0:01:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon Detective Kusukawa's request, Hattori, Uncle and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:51.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,went to Morozumi Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house on the 4th block of Haido City.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.41,0:01:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but she declined the investigation for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.33,0:02:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You said you were coming back because you were done with all of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.09,0:02:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we were, but some fire trucks passed us on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.88,0:02:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got worried, so we went back, and found out that it was on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.44,0:02:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Red Horse within the Flames,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.40,0:02:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Investigation Part!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.24,0:02:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously! What is that idiot doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.78,0:02:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just when I finally found a shirt that would fit Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.62,0:02:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now... I'm sure they'll be back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.17,0:02:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this key holder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.42,0:02:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.29,0:02:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got it from that nice man on the bus when we were riding home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.67,0:02:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, the guy who gave up his seat because he thought my bags were heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.22,0:02:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry for troubling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.60,0:02:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.97,0:02:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, where do you two live?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.27,0:02:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister, are you hitting on us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.89,0:02:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:03:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,-It's not that. I run an antique store in Haido and I wanted you to visit some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.19,0:03:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's in Haido, I'm very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My house is on the fifth block of Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.82,0:03:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? The 5th block, you say...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.70,0:03:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want to go tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.99,0:03:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.12,0:03:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, 'll give you our catalog and a key holder as a present.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.87,0:03:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Promise me you'll come.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.71,0:03:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how is this key holder supposed to bring prosperity?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.63,0:03:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.76,0:03:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the four red horses that were left at the crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.60,0:03:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm bending the rules to let you see them, so you'd better find some clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.98,0:03:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it wasn't me who wanted to see it, it was these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.65,0:03:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why is this one charred so much more than the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.90,0:03:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, it's the only one that has a base.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.32,0:03:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? There's something written on the bottom of the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.87,0:03:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.37,0:03:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey isn't "red horse" and "rabbit"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.91,0:04:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.25,0:04:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, isn't this Guan Yu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.75,0:04:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the great warrior from Three Kingdoms?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.75,0:04:11.51,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: "The Records of Three Kingdoms (Sanguo Zhi) is a Chinese text which covers the period of Three Kingdoms from 189 AD to 280 AD.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.05,0:04:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Guan Yu is also famous as a god of chivalry and prosperity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, he's riding on a really vividly colored horse, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because this is the famous Red Hare horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.01,0:04:20.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an amazing horse that can run 4000 kilometers a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.10,0:04:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Red Hare?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.77,0:04:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying this plastic red horse is the famous horse from Three Kingdoms?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.61,0:04:30.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.15,0:04:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look at the bottom of the base attached to the horse from the first crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.99,0:04:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first and last kanji are illegible, but you can still see that "rabbit" was written in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.83,0:04:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.67,0:04:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to a red horse with "rabbit" in it's name,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.09,0:04:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,can you think of anything else but the Red Hare from Three Kingdoms?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.84,0:04:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did the arsonist leave a legendary horse from Chinese literature at each scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.97,0:04:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.64,0:05:04.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of China, Feng Shui is also a branch of classic Chinese study.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who came to visit Morozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s home,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.98,0:05:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,did he mention anything about that ancient Chinese story to Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.74,0:05:17.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although he didn't mention the Three Kingdoms, that Feng Shui teacher has a solid motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.49,0:05:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That teacher was desperately looking for a video tape that proved he and the deceased Morozumi Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were having an affair with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think he set the house on fire in order to destroy the tape in the process?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.38,0:05:34.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yuminaga...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.85,0:05:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good, let me know immediately if you find anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.02,0:05:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the teacher isn't the only one with a motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.90,0:05:54.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Gondou Keiko, the fortune-teller who visited the house after the Feng Shui teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.15,0:06:00.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,is entitled to inherit a very large estate from the death of her sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, the fortune-teller lady said her father had just passed away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, she was asking Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.04,0:06:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she was about to inherit her father's estate, why would she do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.76,0:06:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her father had left a will which said that out of his two daughters, Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Keiko,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,everything would be left to Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the one who carried on the Morozumi family name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.69,0:06:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:35.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} gone, Keiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would get the estate she wasn't supposed to inherit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.53,0:06:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.32,0:06:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, Japanese law requires the will to specifically state if a family member is not to be included in the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.08,0:06:48.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband can't be a suspect, since he'd lose a large fortune without his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.21,0:06:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we can't assume that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.71,0:07:00.05,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The husband, Morozumi Akira, is a psychiatrist, and has been hoping to destroy the house to build a clinic there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.05,0:07:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was strongly against the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.31,0:07:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, the land had been inherited from her parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, if he had known about his wife's affair, he has a viable motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.69,0:07:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that all three of them have alibis is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.62,0:07:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, it was around 7:30 PM when the arsonist started the fire and placed the horse on the windowsill.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.04,0:07:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The husband got home about ten minutes earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.42,0:07:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but left within a minute to go drinking with the Feng Shui teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.63,0:07:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, the fortune-telling lady was at the convention by Haido Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only suspect left is the man who was already at the door when we first arrived at Morozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:08:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The antique dealer who tried to give Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} a catalog and a key holder from his store,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.57,0:08:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but was screamed at and turned away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.08,0:08:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, unless we know who and where he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.33,0:08:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what do you think this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, there is a weird lump at the center of the first horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.47,0:08:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a human foot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.68,0:08:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was melted by the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it looks like a person was riding on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.64,0:08:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't there a warrior who rode the Red Hare?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.64,0:08:30.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.85,0:08:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Um... was it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.60,0:08:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,G-Guan Yu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.06,0:08:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guan Yu?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.19,0:08:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man with round glasses is even more suspicious now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.49,0:08:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guan Yu is a god of prosperity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.61,0:08:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key holder boxes he was handing out is just about the right size for this horse to fit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.41,0:08:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? I was sure the rider of the Red Hare was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.79,0:08:59.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing? You've got to call every single antique shop near Haido.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.63,0:09:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry, he'll get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.01,0:09:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By any chance, is the man you saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.39,0:09:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By any chance, is the man you saw... this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.43,0:09:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it, it's already past 11:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.73,0:09:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to Tropical Land tomorrow, so I didn't think they wouldn't be coming home tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.73,0:09:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously, what are they doing out this late with Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.45,0:09:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.11,0:09:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's forget about them and go to bed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.41,0:09:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.78,0:09:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think we should hang it above Dad's veranda so it won't rain tomorrow, just in case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.41,0:09:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The teruterubozu, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.17,0:09:37.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't seem to work last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.55,0:09:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll ask it properly tonight, so that it'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.55,0:09:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.39,0:09:50.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I found you. I finally found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.35,0:09:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! He's already been suspected once during the investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.23,0:09:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.56,0:09:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, his name is Genda Takanori.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.65,0:10:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you've guessed, he runs an antique store in Haido.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.86,0:10:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did you suspect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.82,0:10:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was among the crowd of onlookers in the first case in Rizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.66,0:10:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While looking at the fire, he was mumbling something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.12,0:10:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was saying "Father, Father..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Father"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.67,0:10:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His father was a firefighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.01,0:10:30.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He died in the line of duty, while trying to save someone from a fire when Genda was still in elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.85,0:10:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the guy could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.89,0:10:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we thought of the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.06,0:10:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He might have set the fire out of longing for his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.36,0:10:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's conceivable that he believed his father would appear if there was a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.70,0:10:56.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So, when the first one didn't grant his wish,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.75,0:11:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he continued to set fires one by one, chasing the illusion of his father's return.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He went home around 5:00 PM, after stopping by the store?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.84,0:11:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he said he was tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.64,0:11:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The manager had been out delivering catalogs and complimentary key holders on foot since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By any chance, could that key holder have a red horse...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.81,0:11:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean the manager's masterpiece, Guan Yu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.23,0:11:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't receive very positive feedback, so he changed it to a different key holder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.57,0:11:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.66,0:11:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The one he gave out today should be of a manekineko.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.83,0:11:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there anything wrong with the manager, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.54,0:11:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, no. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.96,0:11:43.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so mad, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.17,0:11:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think we'll be able to leave for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.30,0:11:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, you're familiar with the Three Kingdoms, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.47,0:11:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.76,0:11:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lu Bu was the the warrior who rode the Red Hare, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.47,0:12:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, but the Red Hare later fell into Cao Cao's hands, and then became Guan Yu's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.19,0:12:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was even given a key holder with Guan Yu riding the Red Hare today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.86,0:12:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You were given a key holder with Guan Yu riding the Red Hare?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.07,0:12:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.45,0:12:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle... which block is the detective agency on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.41,0:12:16.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.12,0:12:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm asking you which block it's on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.45,0:12:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-Th-The 5th block...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.79,0:12:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.38,0:12:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't quite understand, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.92,0:12:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he's on his way home now, and told us to not go outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.22,0:12:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been hearing strange noises coming from the front door for a while. They're kind of freaking me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.02,0:12:49.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Genda's home is in Rizen?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.94,0:12:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.57,0:12:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw him near the Morozumi house in Haido around 7:30 PM, when Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband came home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.95,0:13:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran must've taken the bus that goes through Haido, Beika, and Rizen, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.21,0:13:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really did plan to go home at first, but then returned to the store for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.72,0:13:17.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, wasn't the first arson case in Rizen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.97,0:13:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was near his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that the owners were close to him and were some of his best customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.23,0:13:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it's possible that he burned down the house so that no one would find out his antiques were fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.57,0:13:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.87,0:13:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you keep such a suspicious person in custody?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.29,0:13:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I've just lost my edge as an officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.67,0:13:54.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a patrol car in front of the detective agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.47,0:13:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.64,0:14:05.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genda!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.73,0:14:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.61,0:14:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.40,0:14:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you called, that man came and said we had to return the key holder he had given to us on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.78,0:14:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we asked "Why?", he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.28,0:14:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll become a fire, can't help but set the place on fire again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.46,0:14:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then he burst into tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.71,0:14:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do anything but dial 110...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.80,0:14:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Genda... is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.63,0:14:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it really you who started those fires?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.47,0:14:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.48,0:14:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Inspector Yuminaga, we'll take the suspect to Beika Station for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.85,0:14:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.07,0:14:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the very least, he's willing to confess to his crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.53,0:15:02.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hattori, doesn't this seem familiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.53,0:15:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was just thinking the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.04,0:15:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one of the most famous books in the Hercule Poirot detective series...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.38,0:15:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just like The ABC Murders!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.96,0:15:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man killed random individuals whose names started with A, B, and C in alphabetical order.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.09,0:15:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He left an ABC Railway Guide beside the bod of each victim to make them seem like serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.43,0:15:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All to disguise the murder of his true target, a person whose name began with C.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.32,0:15:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This trick is really similar to the way that man used apparent random serial murders to hide who his intended victim was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.20,0:15:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the man who turned himself in just now is a meek salesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.12,0:15:55.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just like the man who was arrested in the novel, being forced to believe he was the killer by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.42,0:15:58.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems a more thorough investigation is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.09,0:16:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. At the 4th block where the scent of the trick is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.10,0:16:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.06,0:16:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going back to last night's crime scene at the 4th block of Haido!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.94,0:16:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. There's something about it that bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.23,0:16:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I'm thinking of taking this kid with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.32,0:16:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget the stupid fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're supposed to go to Tropical Land together today, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.74,0:16:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if it's Tropic or Arctic, this case is more than what it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.70,0:16:31.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the case is closed. The arsonist was arrested last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.21,0:16:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right! It's that guy with the round glasses that gave us the Red Hare key holder!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.13,0:16:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. There's a chance that the real culprit might have that guy under mind control.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.72,0:16:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mind control?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.64,0:16:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morozumi Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is a psychiatrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.64,0:16:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soga Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is a Feng Shui teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.60,0:16:57.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Gondo Keiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is a fortune-teller.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.11,0:17:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three have the potential to manipulate the human mind, as well as motives for starting the fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.03,0:17:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think they're suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.99,0:17:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, those three all have alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.62,0:17:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I want to go down there to confirm them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.91,0:17:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows? We might discover the truth that's hidden beneath the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.75,0:17:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really is... Why would anyone want to come to a scary place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.51,0:17:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why'd you come!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.97,0:17:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What other choice was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.60,0:17:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We want you to hurry and solve this case so we can go to Tropical Land together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, we're also a bit curious about the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.56,0:17:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.60,0:17:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brought a lot of assistants with you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.44,0:17:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.19,0:17:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, did Genda confess?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.53,0:17:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All he said was, "I don't know."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.78,0:17:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I don't know?"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.74,0:17:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... According to Genda, he has a split personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.83,0:17:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thinks it's possible that his other personality caused him to set fire to the buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.08,0:17:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, he used to sleepwalk during his childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.92,0:18:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that habit seems to have resurfaced recently, so he was seeing a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.30,0:18:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that psychiatrist be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.09,0:18:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was Morozumi Akira.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.68,0:18:14.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears he had been prescribing him anti-anxiety drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.60,0:18:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he was quite surprised when he heard that Genda had turned himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.23,0:18:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, that Soga guy was also surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.15,0:18:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soga and Genda often bump into each other at antique markets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.28,0:18:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where Soga recommended Morozumi's clinic to Genda.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.91,0:18:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soga Misao is a strange man who dropped out of medical school in order to pursue a career in Feng Shui.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.67,0:18:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day, Genda went to Morozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s home...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.92,0:18:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because Soga told him that visiting that part of the neighborhood would grant him good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.30,0:18:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it's just like Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.59,0:18:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They all had some connection to Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.43,0:18:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, is it possible that Genda would have some connection with the fortune teller, Gondo Keiko, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:19:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't checked that yet, however she's highly suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.36,0:19:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body was discovered at the scene, she was holding this small cushion in her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.11,0:19:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning, when we asked those three to come down to the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.66,0:19:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she suddenly turned pale and tried to leave whenever I asked her about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.75,0:19:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, isn't that a dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.63,0:19:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you let her go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.76,0:19:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already have a man in custody, and the woman has an alibi, so we couldn't stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.43,0:19:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, if you're right about the time of the arson.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.47,0:19:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanna go ask yourself? The witness is the boy next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.48,0:19:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, it's really true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.57,0:19:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw a really big horse shadow on the living room curtain when the opening theme to Kamen Yaiba was playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.87,0:19:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.95,0:20:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure. I turned on the light when I came into the living room at shortly after 7:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.88,0:20:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I don't know if there was a shadow or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.71,0:20:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.34,0:20:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, do you mind if we see the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.51,0:20:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.97,0:20:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that means this is the curtain that the horse's shadow was cast onto.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.77,0:20:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.94,0:20:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was your son watching TV in the dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.15,0:20:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems it's popular among the children in this neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.45,0:20:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's cool 'cause it's like being at the movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.28,0:20:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, kid... you have to turn the lights on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.83,0:20:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, your eyesight will go bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.16,0:20:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.84,0:20:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it's possible the shadow was projected before 7:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the light that flames give off is sporadic, the shadows they cast are constantly changing their shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.30,0:20:58.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it might not have looked like a horse until you saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.81,0:21:00.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.02,0:21:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until the clock on top of the TV said it was time for Kamen Yaiba, I was watching baseball the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.11,0:21:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only time it got bright outside, and the horse appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was during Yaiba's opening theme.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.07,0:21:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you watched the baseball game in the dark, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.87,0:21:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.83,0:21:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if it was dark, you wouldn't be able to see the clock above the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.46,0:21:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could. The outside of the window was lit up a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.17,0:21:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The horse's shadow wasn't wobbling either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.97,0:21:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Heiji!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.51,0:21:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.10,0:21:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look closer, Hattori. They've got to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.81,0:21:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, the evidence that backs up our deduction is definitely around here somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.31,0:21:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.40,0:21:48.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A burned-out light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.32,0:21:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found what I was looking for, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.23,0:21:54.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The remains of several pieces of burnt tissue paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.65,0:21:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're right then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.03,0:22:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, with this, it's possible to start the fire without being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.54,0:22:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All we need to do now is figure out how the culprit controlled Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.83,0:22:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,find the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.23,0:23:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.65,0:23:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They match perfectly with the shoe in the shoe rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.90,0:23:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's some strange things in the trash can.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.74,0:24:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pair of muddy socks and a partly burnt shirt...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.28,0:24:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.83,0:24:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't a listening device.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.24,0:24:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of that, we found something unbelievable.
